## Disable the BEAM break handler so Ctrl+C exits the CLI immediately
## instead of presenting the BREAK: (a)bort menu.
+Bd

## The skein binary is a CLI, not an interactive Erlang node: never boot
## the Erlang shell. With a shell attached to the TTY, its line editor
## competes with the Raxol TUI driver for stdin — keys never reach the
## TUI and Ctrl-C then kills the VM mid-TUI without terminal cleanup
## (issue #171 macOS verification). This also stops every TTY invocation
## from flashing the Erlang banner.
-noshell
